<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-605-355  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 605 355.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  Nov 18 1990 v140 p21(N) p21(L) 17 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer problems delay installation of new weather radar.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An advanced weather radar system for the National Weather Serviceis delayed by production problems.andP;  The system, which would allowweather forecasters to view weather systems in motion, woulddetect tornadoes before they strike and improve other types offorecasting.andP;  Three Federal departments - Commerce, Transportationand Defense - have contracted to buy a total of 165 of the devicesfor $359 million.andP;  Most are for the Weather Service, which is partof the Commerce Department.andP;  Government officials are concernedabout an uncertain financial situation at Unisys Corp, whichmanufactures the systems.andP;  Unisys has large debts, and the companyreported a $356.8 million deficit in the 3rd qtr.andP;  The company didnot pay a dividend to shareholders this year, and it has announcedthat it will eliminate 5,000 jobs.andP;  So far, Unisys's financialproblems are apparently not related to delays in installing radarsystems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    UIS.andO;Topic:     MeteorologyGovernment ContractsComputer industryRadar Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>